'''George Buza''' (born [[January 7]], [[1940s#1949|1949]]) is an actor whose first role was playing Gregg in one episode of ''Kung Fu''. He later appeared on other live-action films and series like ''Highpoint'', ''Seeing Things'' and ''The Amateur''. Meanwhile he started voicing his first character, [[Chief/Legends|Chief]] [[Chirpa/Legends|Chirpa]], in the first [[Ewoks (television series)|''Ewoks'']] season. A decade later he was a frequent guest star on Fox Kids' ''X-Men'' and appeared on four episodes of ''Mythic Warriors''. His other appearances in cartoon animation were ''Spider-Man'' and ''Beyblade''.

Born in Cleveland, Ohio, Buza grew up in Canada. After his grandfather took him to the movies, he decided when still a boy that he wanted to be an actor. In 1998 he became a Canadian citizen.

